headline: A $576 Billion Stock-ETF Juggernaut Hit by Extreme Dislocations
summary: (Bloomberg) -- One of the largest exchange-traded funds in the world was left at the widest premium to its underlying holdings since 2008 at the end of Wednesday’s historic session.In another sign of the frantic trading on Wall Street, the $576 billion SPDR S&P 500 ETF Trust, or SPY, closed roughly 90 basis points above its net-asset value on a day when it surged 10.5% — the most in 16 years — data compiled by Bloomberg show. headline: State Street Global Advisors Announces State Street Target Retirement IndexPlus, Providing Defined Contribution Investors Access to Both Public and Private Markets Exposures
summary: BOSTON, April 10, 2025--State Street Global Advisors, the asset management business of State Street Corporation (NYSE: STT), today announced the launch of its State Street Target Retirement IndexPlus Strategy, which will provide access to both public and private market exposures in a diversified strategy for defined contribution plans and their participants.
